<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

<h3>What is a martial arts CRM?</h3>

<p>A martial arts CRM is a customer relationship management system designed for martial arts schools. It handles lead capture and nurturing, trial class management, student engagement tracking, retention monitoring, and communication management throughout the student lifecycle.</p>

<h3>How does a martial arts CRM differ from generic CRM software?</h3>

<p>Martial arts CRM includes features specific to the industry: trial class scheduling, belt progression as an engagement metric, family account relationships, attendance-based retention alerts, and integration with martial arts management functions. Generic CRMs lack these purpose-built capabilities.</p>

<h3>What lead management features should martial arts CRM include?</h3>

<p>Essential features include: website form integration for lead capture, pipeline stage tracking, trial class scheduling and tracking, automated follow-up sequences, source attribution for marketing analysis, and conversion reporting.</p>

<h3>How can CRM improve student retention?</h3>

<p>CRM improves retention through attendance decline alerts, engagement scoring, automated re-engagement communications, milestone recognition, and providing complete relationship history so staff can have informed conversations with at-risk students.</p>

<h3>Is martial arts CRM separate from management software?</h3>

<p>CRM functionality is typically integrated within comprehensive martial arts management software rather than as a separate system. This integration ensures data flows between lead management, scheduling, billing, and communication functions.</p>

<h3>How do I measure martial arts CRM success?</h3>

<p>Key metrics include: lead-to-trial conversion rate, trial-to-enrolment conversion rate, student retention rate, average student tenure, lifetime value, and cost per acquisition. Tracking these before and after CRM implementation quantifies impact.</p>

<h3>Can CRM track referrals from existing students?</h3>

<p>Yes, quality CRM tracks referral sources, linking new leads to referring students. This enables referral programme management, reward distribution, and analysis of which students generate the most referrals.</p>

<h3>What automated communications should CRM send?</h3>

<p>Effective automation includes: trial confirmation and reminders, post-trial follow-up sequences, welcome series for new students, attendance decline outreach, membership renewal reminders, milestone celebrations, and re-engagement campaigns for inactive students.</p>

